  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to investigate how the commonly used anesthetic drug propofol
      works in the brain to produce loss of consciousness. While under general anesthesia your
      brain waves will be measured using electroencephalogram (EEG). On a separate day, the
      patient's brain will be imaged using magnetic resonance imaging (MRI).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
